262
00:20:59,730 --> 00:21:02,149
You can't advance here
unless you're part of it.

263
00:21:02,233 --> 00:21:06,070
Every director in the history
of the Bureau has come from
the law enforcement side.

264
00:21:06,153 --> 00:21:08,614
The guys who shoot,
the guys who make arrests.

265
00:21:08,697 --> 00:21:10,949
There's never
been a director
from the Intel side.

266
00:21:11,033 --> 00:21:12,200
Never will be.

267
00:21:12,242 --> 00:21:13,994
Intel's Siberia.
Sir.

268
00:21:14,077 --> 00:21:15,995
The rubber gun squad.

269
00:21:16,079 --> 00:21:17,580
So why did you stay?
Huh?

270
00:21:17,997 --> 00:21:21,626
All those years, why didn't
you transfer into something
with a higher profile?

271
00:21:22,126 --> 00:21:24,962
Because I never cared
about making headlines.

272
00:21:25,087 --> 00:21:26,880
I wanted to make history.
Sorry.

273
00:21:27,131 --> 00:21:31,927
The people Intel tracks
are the ones who want to
wipe America off the map.

274
00:21:32,719 --> 00:21:36,389
Somehow that always meant
a little more to me
than being promoted.

275
00:21:41,561 --> 00:21:44,647
Why are you reading
about Parkinson's?

276
00:21:45,397 --> 00:21:46,482
My mother.

277
00:21:46,607 --> 00:21:47,566
Oh.

278
00:21:47,649 --> 00:21:49,276
For a few years now.

279
00:21:50,652 --> 00:21:52,904
I'm very sorry
to hear about that.

280
00:21:57,408 --> 00:21:58,493
Good morning.

281
00:22:03,497 --> 00:22:04,623
Morning.

282
00:22:08,544 --> 00:22:12,339
Oh, I forgot to mention, sir,
we got a call from Photo,
about a portrait sitting.

283
00:22:12,547 --> 00:22:15,008
You're going up on the
"25 Years of Service" wall.

284
00:22:16,843 --> 00:22:18,428
Imagine that.

285
00:22:22,348 --> 00:22:23,933
Excuse me.

286
00:22:30,063 --> 00:22:31,106
Lord.

287
00:22:35,402 --> 00:22:36,611
Beautiful woman.

288
00:22:37,237 --> 00:22:38,446
You're married.

289
00:22:38,529 --> 00:22:40,114
I can look, can't I?

290
00:22:41,866 --> 00:22:46,537
God expects you
to live your faith, Eric,
at all times.

291
00:22:47,204 --> 00:22:50,666
Besides, I disapprove
of women in pantsuits.

292
00:22:51,541 --> 00:22:52,834
You do?

293
00:22:53,418 --> 00:22:55,128
Men wear pants.

294
00:22:55,628 --> 00:22:58,965
The world doesn't need
any more Hillary Clintons.

295
00:23:01,968 --> 00:23:05,387
I wrote a program
last night using nothing
but ones and zeroes

296
00:23:05,554 --> 00:23:07,139
just to see
if I could do it.

297
00:23:08,140 --> 00:23:11,810
Six-hundred twelve bits
of encryption,
completely unbreakable.

298
00:23:12,394 --> 00:23:14,729
But you get the office
with the window.

299
00:23:18,024 --> 00:23:20,151
Okay, help us.
What do we do?

300
00:23:26,907 --> 00:23:30,619
First, we drop ACS,
which is a relic.

301
00:23:30,702 --> 00:23:32,621
There's not nearly
enough bandwidth.

302
00:23:33,205 --> 00:23:34,372
That's why
you've got agents

303
00:23:34,414 --> 00:23:37,250
who still keep
sensitive information
in cardboard boxes.

304
00:23:39,001 --> 00:23:42,380
You need to move
to an ATM system
instead of the WAN.

305
00:23:42,963 --> 00:23:44,256
An OC-48

306
00:23:44,507 --> 00:23:48,302
with a data rate
of 2.488 megabits.

307
00:23:49,595 --> 00:23:53,348
Start with Linux A-B servers,
which puts us into Red Hat.

308
00:23:53,932 --> 00:23:56,100
IP routers
throughout the building.

309
00:23:56,559 --> 00:24:00,730
Dynamic IP addresses
to hide the system using
the Invicta prototype.

310
00:24:02,106 --> 00:24:04,316
Would it be easier
if I sent this in a memo?

311
00:24:04,358 --> 00:24:07,236
Yes, it would.
Fine. On your desk
in the morning.

312
00:24:07,694 --> 00:24:09,613
You're gonna set up
meetings for me

313
00:24:09,696 --> 00:24:14,159
with the appropriate
systems managers
at the CIA, DIA, NSA,

314
00:24:14,242 --> 00:24:16,494
and the intel agencies
of each armed service.

315
00:24:16,536 --> 00:24:17,662
Yes, sir.

316
00:24:17,745 --> 00:24:20,790
They're all
ahead of us on IT.
We have to study them.

317
00:24:20,873 --> 00:24:24,793
Would you mind if we
book those appointments
through me, Bob?

318
00:24:25,336 --> 00:24:26,628
What for?

319
00:24:27,171 --> 00:24:28,213
Just protocol.

320
00:24:28,380 --> 00:24:29,590
Of course.

321
00:24:30,299 --> 00:24:32,217
And then we switch
offices, right?

322
00:24:33,218 --> 00:24:34,177
Sure.

323
00:24:34,302 --> 00:24:37,388
Perfect.
We're fighting crime
with 19th-century technology,

324
00:24:37,430 --> 00:24:39,390
and he's worried
about protocol.

325
00:24:39,932 --> 00:24:42,685
Set up those meetings.
Leave it up to him,
they'll never happen.

326
00:24:42,768 --> 00:24:43,769
Sir?

327
00:24:43,853 --> 00:24:46,063
That was turf protection
you were just watching
in there.

328
00:24:46,146 --> 00:24:48,982
Didn't you spot it?
Organizational arrogance.

329
00:24:49,024 --> 00:24:51,568
"No, we don't want to learn
anything from the CIA.

330
00:24:51,651 --> 00:24:53,153
"We want the CIA
answering to us."

331
00:24:55,488 --> 00:24:57,198
You know what's going on
behind that door?

332
00:24:57,323 --> 00:24:58,449
No, sir.

333
00:24:58,533 --> 00:25:02,536
Analysts looking
for a spy inside the
intelligence community.

334
00:25:02,703 --> 00:25:04,079
Highest clearance.

335
00:25:04,163 --> 00:25:07,249
But there aren't any
CIA officers in there.
You know why?

336
00:25:07,291 --> 00:25:10,377
Because it's a CIA officer
we're trying to build
a case against.

337
00:25:10,919 --> 00:25:14,255
Now, could the mole be
someone from the Bureau
and not the CIA?

338
00:25:14,339 --> 00:25:15,298
Of course.

339
00:25:15,381 --> 00:25:17,050
Are we actively pursuing
that possibility?

340
00:25:17,133 --> 00:25:18,259
Of course not.

341
00:25:18,343 --> 00:25:20,845
'Cause we're the Bureau,
and the Bureau knows all.

342
00:25:26,809 --> 00:25:32,439
Cooperation is
counter-operational.
And that's the mentality.

343
00:25:32,939 --> 00:25:35,692
Of course, the enemies
of this country
aren't so picky.

344
00:25:36,109 --> 00:25:38,820
They'll work with anyone
who shares their hatred of us.

345
00:25:39,278 --> 00:25:41,864
Bureau hasn't learned
that lesson yet.

346
00:25:51,748 --> 00:25:54,334
He keeps some paintings
in a conference room on 8.

347
00:25:54,376 --> 00:25:55,835
I want you to get
one of them for me.

348
00:25:56,794 --> 00:26:00,047
Sir?
It's two men on a boat.
I want it.

349
00:26:01,215 --> 00:26:04,093
What? You mean Agent Garces?
These are his paintings.

350
00:26:04,176 --> 00:26:05,886
Stop thinking
like a clerk.

351
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:07,638
They're sitting
in storage.

352
00:26:08,555 --> 00:26:10,474
It's two guys on a boat.

353
00:26:13,643 --> 00:26:16,229
BURROUGHS: Okay.
Where was Hanssen
on March 7, 1991?

354
00:26:16,312 --> 00:26:19,482
The file has him
making a drop at Ellis
at 6:30 p.m.

355
00:26:22,443 --> 00:26:27,072
He badged in at 8:27 a.m.
Badged out at 12:45.

356
00:26:27,156 --> 00:26:29,825
Badged back in at 1:45,

357
00:26:29,950 --> 00:26:32,369
and badged out again at 5:36.

358
00:26:32,452 --> 00:26:35,955
Okay. Let's take a look
at August 12, 1993.

359
00:26:42,628 --> 00:26:45,506
You know why the Soviet
Empire collapsed?

360
00:26:48,383 --> 00:26:49,718
"Good morning"?

361
00:26:49,760 --> 00:26:51,803
I made a career
studying them.

362
00:26:52,512 --> 00:26:53,972
They were smarter
than us.

363
00:26:54,848 --> 00:26:57,558
More devious,
more determined.

364
00:26:58,393 --> 00:27:00,144
So why did they fail?

365
00:27:03,397 --> 00:27:04,899
Godlessness.

366
00:27:06,150 --> 00:27:07,443
Atheism.

367
00:27:10,570 --> 00:27:13,031
I'm on my way
to morning Mass.

368
00:27:13,114 --> 00:27:14,824
You do remember
what Mass is, yes?

369
00:27:15,366 --> 00:27:18,369
The Jesuits at Gonzaga
taught you that much,
didn't they?

370
00:27:18,411 --> 00:27:20,163
Sir, my grandfather
was a deacon.

371
00:27:22,915 --> 00:27:24,959
Well, congratulations.

372
00:27:26,418 --> 00:27:28,670
Now it's time
to join the varsity.

373
00:27:32,591 --> 00:27:36,427
I saw a woman from
Planned Parenthood
on television this morning.

374
00:27:37,178 --> 00:27:40,348
A lesbian, naturally.
Defending gay marriage.

375
00:27:42,099 --> 00:27:44,310
I almost ripped the cable
out of the wall.

376
00:27:45,269 --> 00:27:47,354
Bet she was
wearing pants, huh?

377
00:27:53,318 --> 00:27:56,696
Will your children
be Jesuit-taught,
as you were?

378
00:27:57,864 --> 00:28:01,576
I don't know yet.
That conversation's
still a few years away.

379
00:28:02,076 --> 00:28:03,202
It shouldn't be.

380
00:28:03,285 --> 00:28:04,537
Sir, I'm GS-11.

381
00:28:04,578 --> 00:28:06,538
We need a second salary
before we can start having...

382
00:28:06,622 --> 00:28:09,041
What is money
compared with
the blessings of family?

383
00:28:09,458 --> 00:28:10,417
Tell me.

384
00:28:11,293 --> 00:28:13,670
My wife was the one...
Good to see you, Bob.

385
00:28:15,880 --> 00:28:18,383
It was my wife
who first brought me here.

386
00:28:18,466 --> 00:28:19,425
Bonnie.

387
00:28:20,384 --> 00:28:23,971
I was a Lutheran when we met,
and not much of one.

388
00:28:24,763 --> 00:28:26,682
She saved my life.

389
00:28:27,933 --> 00:28:29,017
Come.

390
00:29:16,269 --> 00:29:18,479
We attend St. Catherine's
on Sundays.

391
00:29:19,355 --> 00:29:21,482
It's a traditional
Latin service,

392
00:29:21,565 --> 00:29:23,192
then a big
family lunch after.

393
00:29:24,276 --> 00:29:26,653
You think Juliana
might like that?

394
00:29:27,571 --> 00:29:29,615
I don't know. Maybe.

395
00:29:30,198 --> 00:29:33,201
Then let's give it a try.
This weekend.

396
00:29:34,536 --> 00:29:37,205
My Bonnie's been known
to work miracles.

397
00:29:41,834 --> 00:29:42,877
(PAGER BEEPING)

398
00:29:42,960 --> 00:29:45,045
Shut that off.
Sorry.

399
00:29:49,675 --> 00:29:51,301
Was that your wife?

400
00:29:52,093 --> 00:29:54,346
No one else
even has this number.

401
00:29:56,097 --> 00:29:59,809
Well, perhaps
you should give her a call.
It might be important.

402
00:30:00,601 --> 00:30:03,646
No, it's okay.
It can wait.

403
00:30:15,698 --> 00:30:16,950
BURROUGHS: You know,
when I page you,

404
00:30:17,075 --> 00:30:18,576
<i>it isn't to discuss
what's on Oprah</i>

405
00:30:18,659 --> 00:30:20,203
It means I need
to speak with you.

406
00:30:21,203 --> 00:30:23,247
Did you pick me
because I was Catholic?

407
00:30:23,330 --> 00:30:24,373
I'm sorry?

408
00:30:24,456 --> 00:30:27,793
Did you think
he would trust me
because I was Catholic?

409
00:30:28,669 --> 00:30:30,212
Jesus, Eric.

410
00:30:32,172 --> 00:30:34,758
We picked you
because of your facility
with computers.

411
00:30:34,841 --> 00:30:35,967
We thought it would
impress him.

412
00:30:36,092 --> 00:30:37,051
Uh-huh.

413
00:30:37,260 --> 00:30:39,303
We also thought
he might like
that 50-page proposal

414
00:30:39,387 --> 00:30:41,681
you've been pushing
all over the Bureau.

415
00:30:41,764 --> 00:30:43,974
I understand
he got his hands
on a copy, right?

416
00:30:44,016 --> 00:30:45,059
So?

417
00:30:45,309 --> 00:30:46,769
You got pages for me?

418
00:30:51,398 --> 00:30:53,149
We're going to be
searching his car.

419
00:30:53,233 --> 00:30:56,236
It'll involve you
keeping him out of the office
for a few hours.

420
00:30:59,489 --> 00:31:03,367
Agent Burroughs, I'm starting
to think I might not be
the right guy for this job.

421
00:31:03,451 --> 00:31:06,578
Oh, yeah?
I'm used to intel cases.

422
00:31:07,162 --> 00:31:09,289
Terrorist cases.
Targets of value.

423
00:31:10,207 --> 00:31:13,001
Nobody ever put me
on a perversion
detail before.

424
00:31:13,960 --> 00:31:15,962
Think we're being
too hard on him?

425
00:31:16,629 --> 00:31:18,423
(HORN BLARING)

426
00:31:19,048 --> 00:31:20,466
I think that's your bus.

427
00:31:27,639 --> 00:31:28,599
(DOOR OPENING)

428
00:31:36,648 --> 00:31:37,774
Ta-da!

429
00:31:39,108 --> 00:31:40,818
Will you go
to church with me?

430
00:31:42,945 --> 00:31:43,362
(ORGAN PLAYING)

431
00:31:44,321 --> 00:31:47,658
ALL: "Lord, I am not worthy
that Thou shouldst
come under my roof.

432
00:31:47,908 --> 00:31:51,119
"But only say the word
and my soul shall be healed."

433
00:32:00,294 --> 00:32:01,712
(PRIEST SPEAKING LATIN)

434
00:32:02,296 --> 00:32:03,714
(ALL RESPONDING IN LATIN)

435
00:32:39,414 --> 00:32:40,498
Of course.

436
00:32:47,629 --> 00:32:49,673
Walking, please.
Walking.

437
00:32:50,048 --> 00:32:52,884
Juliana, how did you
like the service?

438
00:32:54,177 --> 00:32:55,595
It was lovely.

439
00:32:56,221 --> 00:32:58,973
I'd never been to a Mass
where people knelt
the whole time.

440
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:02,768
Oh. Well, it's a gesture
of devotion.

441
00:33:04,728 --> 00:33:08,440
Taught all our children
not to be grocery-cart
Catholics.

442
00:33:09,524 --> 00:33:12,736
You know, the kind of
churchgoer that takes
whatever's convenient

443
00:33:12,736 --> 00:33:14,946
and leaves the rest
on the shelf.

444
00:33:16,739 --> 00:33:18,241
It's all expected.

445
00:33:22,620 --> 00:33:24,705
Eric is so nice.

446
00:33:25,956 --> 00:33:27,541
Where did you two meet?

447
00:33:29,960 --> 00:33:31,878
We met in a bar, actually.

448
00:33:32,295 --> 00:33:33,213
Oh.

449
00:33:33,296 --> 00:33:34,506
(CHILDREN CHATTERING)

450
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:39,719
Would you like
some cake, sweetheart?

451
00:33:42,388 --> 00:33:43,597
CHILD: (SQUEALS) My grandfather!

452
00:33:48,101 --> 00:33:49,019
(DOOR OPENING)

453
00:33:59,028 --> 00:34:00,947
I love Sundays.

454
00:34:02,073 --> 00:34:03,699
Going to Mass.

455
00:34:04,116 --> 00:34:05,701
Having the kids here.

456
00:34:06,118 --> 00:34:08,537
Makes everything else
fade away.

457
00:34:08,787 --> 00:34:11,164
Sorry. I was snooping.
Don't be.

458
00:34:11,665 --> 00:34:13,750
I want you to feel
at home here.

459
00:34:15,794 --> 00:34:17,003
Is this
your father, sir?

460
00:34:20,173 --> 00:34:21,632
Must've been
proud of you.

461
00:34:21,716 --> 00:34:24,510
FBI. Top Soviet analyst.
Oh, I don't know.

462
00:34:24,802 --> 00:34:26,387
Father wasn't very

463
00:34:27,054 --> 00:34:28,305
impressed by things.

464
00:34:30,265 --> 00:34:32,309
He wanted me
to be a doctor.

465
00:34:35,645 --> 00:34:39,315
He rigged
my first driving test,
the day I turned 16.

466
00:34:39,857 --> 00:34:43,152
Made an arrangement
with my DMV instructor.

467
00:34:43,402 --> 00:34:44,820
So you'd pass?

468
00:34:44,862 --> 00:34:46,280
So I would fail.

469
00:34:47,239 --> 00:34:49,658
He thought it would
toughen me up.

470
00:34:53,578 --> 00:34:55,205
I do that, too,
I suppose.

471
00:34:55,371 --> 00:34:56,664
Test people.

472
00:34:57,457 --> 00:34:59,042
More than I ought to.

473
00:35:02,795 --> 00:35:05,047
Oh! Shoot.
Almost forgot.

474
00:35:05,297 --> 00:35:07,091
I have something for you.

475
00:35:08,383 --> 00:35:10,260
It's everything I could get
on Parkinson's.

476
00:35:10,385 --> 00:35:12,179
Downloaded it
last night.

477
00:35:13,179 --> 00:35:16,391
Been quite a bit of progress
in the last few years.

478
00:35:16,516 --> 00:35:18,351
Didn't know
if you were up on it.

479
00:35:18,393 --> 00:35:20,645
Is there someone
in your family
who has Parkinson's?

480
00:35:20,686 --> 00:35:22,271
No. No, thank God.

481
00:35:29,111 --> 00:35:31,947
You know, sir, I think
you're misunderstood.

482
00:35:32,113 --> 00:35:33,531
Oh? By whom?

483
00:35:34,949 --> 00:35:37,493
By whoever gives out
window offices, for one.

484
00:35:39,871 --> 00:35:41,789
Oh, that's all right.

485
00:35:42,415 --> 00:35:45,626
I think I made
too much fuss of all that.

486
00:35:47,711 --> 00:35:51,465
I'll be gone so soon anyway,
what good would a window
do me now?

487
00:35:51,631 --> 00:35:55,468
Fifty-seven in two months,
that's mandatory retirement.

488
00:35:55,552 --> 00:35:56,803
(DOG BARKING)

489
00:36:05,561 --> 00:36:07,187
No, it's fine.

490
00:36:07,688 --> 00:36:08,981
It's time.

491
00:36:10,691 --> 00:36:12,817
I could stay there
another hundred years,

492
00:36:12,984 --> 00:36:14,778
and still just be
an afterthought.

493
00:36:17,155 --> 00:36:19,949
The perks go to the guys
who play the game,

494
00:36:20,533 --> 00:36:21,993
the ones who politick.

495
00:36:25,871 --> 00:36:29,333
I knew a long time ago
I didn't have
the stomach for that.

496
00:36:32,627 --> 00:36:36,881
But I'll get my portrait
on that 25-year wall, right?

497
00:36:38,216 --> 00:36:39,801
Now, that's something.

498
00:36:41,802 --> 00:36:44,054
Doesn't really matter
much, does it?

499
00:36:45,347 --> 00:36:48,559
The judgments of other men?

500
00:36:55,106 --> 00:36:56,691
I know what I've done.

501
00:37:25,134 --> 00:37:28,303
What's the trouble?
I want to see
what you got on this guy.

502
00:37:29,846 --> 00:37:32,516
Come again?
His Internet postings,
the e-mails.

503
00:37:32,599 --> 00:37:33,725
Your case.

504
00:37:34,059 --> 00:37:36,686
Why?
Because I don't think
you have one.

505
00:37:39,772 --> 00:37:42,274
I can read you in.
I'm authorized to do that.

506
00:37:42,650 --> 00:37:45,027
But it would only put you
at greater risk.
Of what?

507
00:37:45,110 --> 00:37:46,236
What the hell
is all this?

508
00:37:46,320 --> 00:37:48,572
The guy doesn't drink,
doesn't tell dirty jokes.

509
00:37:48,655 --> 00:37:52,075
Goes to church every day,
his wife loves him,
so do his grandkids.

510
00:37:52,159 --> 00:37:53,868
And why the hell
would you hand
a new division

511
00:37:53,952 --> 00:37:55,328
to a guy who's retiring
in two months,

512
00:37:55,370 --> 00:37:57,372
especially if he's
under investigation?

513
00:37:57,455 --> 00:37:58,539
You through?

514
00:37:58,623 --> 00:38:00,208
You know, I think
this whole thing
is cooked.

515
00:38:00,291 --> 00:38:02,251
I think he keeps
shooting his mouth off
about the Bureau

516
00:38:02,293 --> 00:38:03,627
and nobody knows
what to do with him,

517
00:38:03,711 --> 00:38:05,963
so we tag him as
a deviant and run him
out of the building.

518
00:38:06,046 --> 00:38:07,256
It's bullshit.

519
00:38:07,339 --> 00:38:09,216
The whole thing,
it's Kenneth Starr
all over again,

520
00:38:09,299 --> 00:38:12,511
except I'm running around
looking for the blue dress.

521
00:38:14,763 --> 00:38:16,973
You've come to
admire him, I see.

522
00:38:18,016 --> 00:38:19,142
Yes.

523
00:38:19,767 --> 00:38:20,768
Respect him?

524
00:38:21,227 --> 00:38:22,186
Yes.

525
00:38:23,938 --> 00:38:25,564
Well, that was
inevitable.

526
00:38:26,440 --> 00:38:28,817
For our purposes,
it was sort of necessary.

527
00:38:30,777 --> 00:38:32,237
But he's a traitor, Eric.

528
00:38:33,947 --> 00:38:37,158
He started spying
for the Russians,
we think, in 1985.

529
00:38:40,536 --> 00:38:44,039
He's given them
military secrets,
intelligence secrets.

530
00:38:44,999 --> 00:38:47,292
He gave them our
Continuity of Government
Program,

531
00:38:47,376 --> 00:38:49,002
which told them
where the President
would be taken

532
00:38:49,086 --> 00:38:51,088
during a nuclear
or terrorist attack.

533
00:38:51,171 --> 00:38:55,050
And the Vice President.
And the Congress.
And the Cabinet.

534
00:38:56,551 --> 00:38:59,637
The damage he's done
to the U.S. Government
is in the billions.

535
00:38:59,720 --> 00:39:01,597
But that's just
the money part.

536
00:39:01,681 --> 00:39:03,641
He's also
given up lives.

537
00:39:04,892 --> 00:39:06,435
<i>BURROUGHS:
Sources we were working</i>

538
00:39:09,187 --> 00:39:12,774
<i>In one of his drops,
he identified Valery Martynov
and Sergei Motorin,</i>

539
00:39:12,857 --> 00:39:14,859
<i>two KGB agents we'd turned</i>

540
00:39:21,407 --> 00:39:24,076
<i>They were flown back
to Moscow and executed</i>

541
00:39:28,080 --> 00:39:31,333
We don't have a handle yet
on how many of our assets
he's compromised.

542
00:39:32,250 --> 00:39:34,169
Maybe 50, maybe more.

543
00:39:34,252 --> 00:39:36,212
<i>HANSSEN ON TAPE:
I shouldn't tease you</i>

544
00:39:36,296 --> 00:39:37,922
<i>That just gets me
into trouble</i>

545
00:39:38,172 --> 00:39:40,550
<i>(MAN SPEAKING RUSSIAN)</i>

546
00:39:40,633 --> 00:39:43,094
<i>BURROUGHS:
Our file on him came
from two Russian defectors</i>

547
00:39:43,177 --> 00:39:45,054
<i>The Bureau paid
$7 million for it</i>

548
00:39:45,137 --> 00:39:47,639
<i>Of course,
everything in the file
is inadmissible</i>

549
00:39:47,723 --> 00:39:50,684
<i>We make our own case
independently, or he walks</i>

550
00:39:50,892 --> 00:39:54,020
Oh, not that it matters,
but the sexual stuff
is also true.

551
00:39:54,062 --> 00:39:55,772
Irrelevant, but true.

552
00:39:56,231 --> 00:39:58,316
The stories on the Internet,
they're about his wife.

553
00:39:58,399 --> 00:40:00,276
<i>Using her real name</i>

554
00:40:00,359 --> 00:40:04,613
<i>Sweet little anecdotes about
how much she loves rough sex,
that sort of thing</i>

555
00:40:06,448 --> 00:40:10,702
He's a big fan
of strippers, too.
Has been for years.

556
00:40:14,039 --> 00:40:16,124
But his grandchildren
do love him.

557
00:40:17,292 --> 00:40:19,210
That part I can't argue.

558
00:40:19,961 --> 00:40:22,838
There's no such thing as
the "Information Assurance
Division," is there?

559
00:40:22,922 --> 00:40:24,089
No.

560
00:40:24,632 --> 00:40:27,009
We created that
to lure him back
from State.

561
00:40:27,676 --> 00:40:29,678
<i>9930 was built
for him, too</i>

562
00:40:29,720 --> 00:40:33,515
<i>Video, audio
Bafflers in the vents
Heat sensors Motion sensors</i>

563
00:40:33,848 --> 00:40:36,684
Probably enough
microwaves in that office
to cook a chicken.

564
00:40:38,394 --> 00:40:40,062
<i>I'm sorry we had
to mislead you</i>

565
00:40:40,730 --> 00:40:44,567
But this is the worst
breach in the history
of U.S. Intelligence.

566
00:40:44,733 --> 00:40:46,985
Unusual steps
were required.

567
00:40:48,320 --> 00:40:50,238
The good news is,
you got your wish.

568
00:40:52,991 --> 00:40:56,327
You're in the middle
of the biggest case
we've ever run.

569
00:40:59,539 --> 00:41:02,666
Come with me.
There are some people
I want you to meet.

570
00:41:05,919 --> 00:41:08,922
He badged out at 5:12,
stopped at his dry cleaners,

571
00:41:08,964 --> 00:41:10,966
drove by dead drop Ellis,
then went home.

572
00:41:11,049 --> 00:41:12,842
How does that compare
with the previous Thursday?

573
00:41:12,926 --> 00:41:15,053
WOMAN: Has the Agency
been briefed on this?

574
00:41:15,136 --> 00:41:18,181
If it deals with Russian
sources, then the Agency
has to be briefed on it.

575
00:41:18,264 --> 00:41:20,391
MAN: Does Hanssen have
any leave time coming?

576
00:41:22,476 --> 00:41:24,687
How many people
are working on this?

577
00:41:24,770 --> 00:41:26,689
Got 50 on the
bigot list so far.

578
00:41:27,815 --> 00:41:29,024
Is the Director involved?

579
00:41:29,107 --> 00:41:31,860
Director's running the case.
He sees your pages every day.

580
00:41:31,943 --> 00:41:32,944
No.

581
00:41:33,028 --> 00:41:33,987
Yes.

582
00:41:34,863 --> 00:41:36,364
Keep them coming,
by the way.

583
00:41:36,447 --> 00:41:39,534
Our audio's missing about 90%
of what Hanssen says in there.

584
00:41:39,617 --> 00:41:40,910
He mumbles.

585
00:41:41,410 --> 00:41:43,329
He does a lot of things,
this guy.

586
00:41:44,038 --> 00:41:47,541
Why don't we just
arrest him?
Can't do that.

587
00:41:47,624 --> 00:41:50,836
He knows the names
and locations of every source
we've ever turned.

588
00:41:51,211 --> 00:41:53,880
If we can't get him to talk,
their lives are all at risk.

589
00:41:53,922 --> 00:41:55,548
Eric O'Neill,
Dean Plesac.

590
00:41:55,673 --> 00:41:57,467
Assistant Special Agent
in charge.
Sir.

591
00:41:58,885 --> 00:42:01,470
Director wants him
caught in the act
of making a drop.

592
00:42:01,679 --> 00:42:03,347
That would give you
the death penalty.

593
00:42:03,389 --> 00:42:04,974
Don't you think
he's earned it?

594
00:42:05,057 --> 00:42:07,851
See you, Dean.
Thanks for coming in, Rich.

595
00:42:08,727 --> 00:42:10,812
Like I said, kid,
take nothing personally.

596
00:42:13,940 --> 00:42:15,066
Kate.

597
00:42:16,067 --> 00:42:18,653
He's got an appointment
at the DIA tomorrow
at 2:00, right?

598
00:42:18,736 --> 00:42:20,363
Yeah.
You're driving him?

599
00:42:20,530 --> 00:42:21,739
Yeah.
Good.

600
00:42:21,822 --> 00:42:24,033
We need him out of the office
for at least three hours.

601
00:42:24,074 --> 00:42:26,285
That's when we'll be
sweeping his car.
Okay.

602
00:42:26,660 --> 00:42:29,997
How long will it take you
to download the data card
off his Palm Pilot?

603
00:42:30,080 --> 00:42:32,958
Twenty, 30 minutes,
depending on the level
of encryption.

604
00:42:33,333 --> 00:42:35,752
But you can't.
He never lets it
out of his sight.

605
00:42:37,670 --> 00:42:40,548
Assuming we can separate him
from it, 20 to 30 minutes.

606
00:42:40,631 --> 00:42:41,841
Okay.

607
00:42:49,348 --> 00:42:50,474
What's this?

608
00:42:50,682 --> 00:42:52,184
You want to be
read in, right?

609
00:42:55,728 --> 00:42:57,021
Wait.

610
00:42:58,231 --> 00:43:00,149
What if he's smarter
than I am?

611
00:43:03,569 --> 00:43:06,321
I've never misread anybody
this badly before.

612
00:43:08,615 --> 00:43:09,908
Except maybe you.

613
00:43:13,995 --> 00:43:15,580
A couple of years ago,

614
00:43:16,748 --> 00:43:19,750
the Bureau put together
a task force.

615
00:43:22,461 --> 00:43:24,505
Lots of assets
had been disappearing.

616
00:43:25,381 --> 00:43:29,509
Sources like Motorin,
Martynov. Dozens of them,
vanishing.

617
00:43:29,551 --> 00:43:34,180
So this task force was
formed to find the mole
who was giving them up.

618
00:43:34,347 --> 00:43:38,017
Our best analysts poring
over data for years
looking for the guy,

619
00:43:38,101 --> 00:43:40,978
and they could never
quite find him.

620
00:43:44,190 --> 00:43:46,358
Guess who we put in charge
of the task force?

621
00:43:51,613 --> 00:43:53,365
He was smarter
than all of us.

622
00:43:57,201 --> 00:43:59,579
Actually,
I can live with that part.

623
00:44:01,080 --> 00:44:03,499
It's the idea
that my entire career
has been a waste of time,

624
00:44:03,582 --> 00:44:04,959
that's the part I hate.

625
00:44:05,584 --> 00:44:07,711
Everything I've done
since I got to this office,

626
00:44:07,795 --> 00:44:10,881
everything we've
all been paid to do,
he was undoing it.

627
00:44:11,506 --> 00:44:13,425
We all could have just
stayed home.

628
00:44:19,639 --> 00:44:20,556
(DOOR CLOSING)

629
00:44:29,773 --> 00:44:32,817
<i>HANSSEN: Dear friends,
thank you for the $50,000</i>

630
00:44:33,276 --> 00:44:35,320
<i>As far as the funds
are concerned,</i>

631
00:44:35,403 --> 00:44:39,240
<i>I have little need
or utility for more than
$100,000 at any one time</i>

632
00:44:39,323 --> 00:44:42,368
<i>My security concerns
may seem excessive</i>

633
00:44:42,702 --> 00:44:45,663
<i>I believe experience has
shown them to be necessary</i>

634
00:44:45,704 --> 00:44:49,374
<i>I am much safer
if you know little about me</i>

635
00:44:49,458 --> 00:44:51,042
<i>Neither of us are children
about these things</i>

636
00:44:51,126 --> 00:44:54,963
<i>I was unable to locate
the package based on your
description last night</i>

637
00:44:55,046 --> 00:44:57,548
<i>Please recognize that
I am in a business suit</i>

638
00:44:57,590 --> 00:45:00,259
<i>and cannot slog around
in inch-deep mud</i>

639
00:45:00,343 --> 00:45:03,179
<i>Your service has recently
suffered some setbacks</i>

640
00:45:03,637 --> 00:45:05,806
<i>I warn you that
Mr Boris Yuzhin,</i>

641
00:45:06,098 --> 00:45:09,268
<i>Mr Sergei Motorin
and Mr Valery Martynov</i>

642
00:45:09,309 --> 00:45:11,228
<i>have all been recruited
by our special services</i>

643
00:45:11,311 --> 00:45:15,398
<i>The US can be errantly
likened to a powerfully built,
but retarded child,</i>

644
00:45:15,482 --> 00:45:19,235
<i>potentially dangerous,
but young, immature
and easily manipulated</i>

645
00:45:19,318 --> 00:45:20,945
<i>I found the site empty</i>

646
00:45:20,987 --> 00:45:22,780
<i>Empty sites bother me</i>

647
00:45:22,863 --> 00:45:26,158
<i>I like to know
before I commit myself,
as I'm sure you do also</i>

648
00:45:26,867 --> 00:45:29,786
<i>One might propose that
I am either insanely brave,</i>

649
00:45:30,078 --> 00:45:31,705
<i>or quite insane</i>

650
00:45:32,622 --> 00:45:35,667
<i>I'd answer neither
I'd say insanely loyal</i>

651
00:45:35,708 --> 00:45:38,711
<i>Take your pick,
there's insanity
in all the answers</i>

652
00:45:38,753 --> 00:45:41,922
<i>Eventually, I would
appreciate an escape plan</i>

653
00:45:44,425 --> 00:45:46,343
<i>Nothing lasts forever</i>

654
00:45:48,095 --> 00:45:50,013
<i>Sincerely, Ramon</i>

655
00:45:59,730 --> 00:46:01,357
Hi.
Hi.

656
00:46:06,111 --> 00:46:07,613
You're back.

657
00:46:08,572 --> 00:46:11,450
Boss. When did you
get here?

658
00:46:11,700 --> 00:46:13,493
BONNIE: Very disappointed
in you, young man.

659
00:46:14,077 --> 00:46:17,121
Leaving your bride all alone
without telling her
where you'd be.

660
00:46:17,205 --> 00:46:19,457
Not good, Eric.
Where were you?

661
00:46:20,041 --> 00:46:22,460
My mother fell.
I had to go see her.

662
00:46:23,002 --> 00:46:24,003
Oh.

663
00:46:24,086 --> 00:46:25,629
Did she break anything?

664
00:46:25,754 --> 00:46:28,131
No. Just
bumped her head.

665
00:46:28,924 --> 00:46:30,384
That's awful.
Yeah.

666
00:46:30,675 --> 00:46:32,594
Write down their address
for me, would you?

667
00:46:32,886 --> 00:46:34,304
I'd like to send
some flowers.

668
00:46:34,387 --> 00:46:36,055
That's very kind
of you, boss.

669
00:46:37,515 --> 00:46:39,934
We couldn't reach you
on your pager.

670
00:46:40,601 --> 00:46:42,728
On your hip 24l7,
right?

671
00:46:42,812 --> 00:46:44,688
Yeah, I know.
The battery died.

672
00:46:45,064 --> 00:46:47,024
Sorry, honey.
I should have called.
It's okay.

673
00:46:47,107 --> 00:46:51,027
Juliana was just telling us
what it was like to grow up
in the Communist Bloc.

674
00:46:51,820 --> 00:46:52,862
Oh, yeah?

675
00:46:52,946 --> 00:46:55,824
It piques my curiosity,
as you can imagine.

676
00:46:57,575 --> 00:47:00,536
Hope it hasn't felt
like an interrogation,
Juliana.

677
00:47:02,121 --> 00:47:03,414
(DISHES CLATTERING)
BONNIE: Here we are.

678
00:47:03,747 --> 00:47:05,833
Bonnie, you really
didn't have to go
to all this trouble.

679
00:47:06,583 --> 00:47:07,918
It's just leftovers.

680
00:47:07,960 --> 00:47:09,920
I guess I just couldn't
stand the thought

681
00:47:10,003 --> 00:47:13,590
of you two ordering
from that Peking Wall
place again.

682
00:47:13,840 --> 00:47:17,176
Even Chinese people
can't eat Chinese
every night, Eric.

683
00:47:17,927 --> 00:47:22,306
Besides, how is this
tiny thing going to give you
a house full of babies,

684
00:47:22,348 --> 00:47:24,725
if you don't put some
protein in her diet?

685
00:47:31,231 --> 00:47:33,400
Would you like
to say grace, Eric?

686
00:47:37,236 --> 00:47:38,404
Sweetheart?

687
00:47:45,911 --> 00:47:48,664
I'm sorry, Jule.
I didn't invite them,
obviously.

688
00:47:48,997 --> 00:47:51,249
But they thought
it would be okay, Eric.

689
00:47:51,333 --> 00:47:54,085
You have to have boundaries,
even with a boss.

690
00:47:54,085 --> 00:47:57,213
And what was that
bullshit about your mom
bumping her head?

691
00:47:58,339 --> 00:47:59,882
It's complicated.

692
00:48:00,466 --> 00:48:04,136
"Complicated,"
as in I wouldn't understand,
or as in you can't tell me?

693
00:48:06,889 --> 00:48:08,182
I'm tired.

694
00:48:09,182 --> 00:48:11,393
I just want to grab
a drink and go to bed.

695
00:48:12,477 --> 00:48:14,270
Are you going to quit?

696
00:48:15,021 --> 00:48:16,731
I want you to quit.

697
00:48:17,482 --> 00:48:20,651
I felt sick
all day, Eric.

698
00:48:20,735 --> 00:48:23,028
It's like you're someone else
when he's around.

699
00:48:26,782 --> 00:48:29,117
I'm sorry it's been
a stressful day for you.

700
00:48:29,951 --> 00:48:31,495
Let's not make it worse.

701
00:48:34,414 --> 00:48:35,665
I don't know.

702
00:48:37,166 --> 00:48:38,543
Maybe it's me.

703
00:48:41,462 --> 00:48:44,006
Maybe you want me
to be someone else, too.

704
00:48:44,465 --> 00:48:46,508
Maybe you want me to be
Bonnie or something.

705
00:48:46,592 --> 00:48:47,676
Knock it off, Jule.

706
00:48:47,759 --> 00:48:49,511
No, that'd be easier
for you, wouldn't it?

707
00:48:49,594 --> 00:48:52,138
If I were more of an FBI
kind of wife, like she is.

708
00:48:52,180 --> 00:48:53,515
I'm not kidding, Juliana...

709
00:48:53,598 --> 00:48:56,643
If I just went to church
every day and wanted to spend
my life being pregnant...

710
00:48:56,726 --> 00:48:58,853
Your parents would
probably love that.

711
00:48:58,895 --> 00:49:00,855
Enough.
Then you wouldn't have
to worry anymore

712
00:49:00,938 --> 00:49:03,023
if I was Catholic enough
or American enough.

713
00:49:03,065 --> 00:49:05,317
Shut up, goddamn it!

714
00:49:07,820 --> 00:49:08,779
(DISHES CLATTERING)

715
00:49:17,078 --> 00:49:18,037
(DOOR SLAMS)

716
00:49:40,266 --> 00:49:41,225
Eric.

717
00:49:42,476 --> 00:49:43,602
Hey, Dad.

718
00:49:45,062 --> 00:49:46,647
How long
you been out here?

719
00:49:47,106 --> 00:49:49,358
I don't know.
About an hour or two.

720
00:49:49,941 --> 00:49:52,527
It's freezing.
Why didn't you
let yourself in?

721
00:49:54,112 --> 00:49:55,738
You ever quit
anything, Dad?

722
00:49:55,905 --> 00:49:57,991
Did I ever
quit anything?
Yeah.

723
00:49:59,283 --> 00:50:04,205
I think I gave up
a paper route once.

724
00:50:05,456 --> 00:50:07,666
Got tired of waking up
so early.

725
00:50:08,917 --> 00:50:10,377
What did
your father say?

726
00:50:12,546 --> 00:50:14,881
Nothing.
He just shrugged.

727
00:50:16,758 --> 00:50:18,968
He could kill you
with those shrugs.

728
00:50:20,219 --> 00:50:21,470
(CHUCKLING)

729
00:50:22,680 --> 00:50:25,641
I've been
thinking about him
a lot this morning.

730
00:50:26,350 --> 00:50:28,101
I don't know why.

731
00:50:29,811 --> 00:50:31,688
Well, that's a lot
to put on yourself, son.

732
00:50:31,771 --> 00:50:35,442
I mean, he was just a kid
doing his duty.

733
00:50:36,401 --> 00:50:37,819
Like you.

734
00:50:43,866 --> 00:50:47,411
"Get on the boat,
do your job,
get back home again."

735
00:50:48,787 --> 00:50:49,746
Huh?

736
00:50:51,081 --> 00:50:54,459
That's what he said to me
the first time I shipped out.

737
00:50:55,376 --> 00:50:58,338
He knew I was scared,
so he just kept it simple.

738
00:51:01,549 --> 00:51:03,801
Maybe I should have
gone to Annapolis.

739
00:51:05,594 --> 00:51:08,096
It always seemed to me

740
00:51:09,431 --> 00:51:11,683
that your joining the Bureau
was an apology

741
00:51:11,766 --> 00:51:13,268
for not going
to Annapolis,

742
00:51:13,310 --> 00:51:15,103
which you never
had to do.

743
00:51:15,937 --> 00:51:17,647
It's what you wanted.
No.

744
00:51:18,773 --> 00:51:21,025
I wanted you
to serve your country.

745
00:51:21,400 --> 00:51:23,027
Isn't that
what you're doing?

746
00:51:25,988 --> 00:51:27,322
Yeah.

747
00:51:28,949 --> 00:51:30,826
So you can't quit,
can you?

748
00:51:34,996 --> 00:51:35,955
(SIGHS)

749
00:51:36,331 --> 00:51:39,834
Get on the boat,
do your job,
get back home again.

750
00:51:41,210 --> 00:51:42,545
Can you do that?

751
00:51:52,804 --> 00:51:53,722
(DOOR OPENING)

752
00:51:59,060 --> 00:52:01,729
His appointment's
in 5 minutes.
Media room, 1st floor.

753
00:52:01,771 --> 00:52:03,355
You'll get a page
when he's in-pocket.

754
00:52:03,397 --> 00:52:06,567
Obviously, if he takes
his Palm Pilot with him,
you call me, we shut it down.

755
00:52:06,650 --> 00:52:08,735
It might not be
the best day
to do this, sir.

756
00:52:08,819 --> 00:52:10,278
He's due at the DIA
at 2:00.

757
00:52:10,362 --> 00:52:11,488
I'm driving him.

758
00:52:11,696 --> 00:52:13,573
Looks like you're in
for a full day.

759
00:52:17,076 --> 00:52:19,370
Boss, I just realized
I totally screwed
something up.

760
00:52:19,454 --> 00:52:20,580
Don't you knock?

761
00:52:20,663 --> 00:52:24,083
I'm sorry. The photographer
for your 25-year portrait,
he's here. Today.

762
00:52:24,333 --> 00:52:26,335
I had it in my book
for next week,
but it's today.

763
00:52:26,418 --> 00:52:30,088
They called me on my cell.
Your appointment's
in five minutes.

764
00:52:31,590 --> 00:52:34,259
Then you'll just have to
reschedule, won't you?

765
00:52:34,342 --> 00:52:36,719
We shouldn't.
He's only here once a month.
I'm so sorry.

766
00:52:36,761 --> 00:52:39,388
I'm supposed to drop
everything I'm doing
and run down there?

767
00:52:39,430 --> 00:52:40,890
In this?

768
00:52:41,015 --> 00:52:42,683
That's how you
dress every day.

769
00:52:42,725 --> 00:52:45,477
No. There's a spot
on my tie.

770
00:52:45,561 --> 00:52:46,770
Let me look.

771
00:52:47,646 --> 00:52:49,564
Lord!
Sorry.

772
00:52:49,648 --> 00:52:51,274
You klutz!

773
00:52:52,943 --> 00:52:54,819
Look at that.
It's everywhere.

774
00:52:54,903 --> 00:52:56,738
Boss, please.
Just get down there.

775
00:52:56,821 --> 00:52:58,114
You don't want to
miss your picture.

776
00:52:58,197 --> 00:53:00,199
I'll have all this cleaned up
by the time you get back.

777
00:53:00,241 --> 00:53:02,326
I've got the DIA at 2:00.

778
00:53:02,410 --> 00:53:04,620
I'll get you there.
No problem.

779
00:53:16,839 --> 00:53:19,717
Are you finding
this job stressful, Eric?

780
00:53:20,259 --> 00:53:21,927
Is this all
too much for you?

781
00:53:25,180 --> 00:53:26,473
Sometimes.

782
00:53:29,393 --> 00:53:31,436
Then pray more.

783
00:53:35,482 --> 00:53:36,733
Yes, sir.

784
00:53:50,996 --> 00:53:52,247
(CAMERA CLICKING)

785
00:54:03,924 --> 00:54:07,302
Mr. Hanssen.
Nice to meet you.
I'm John.

786
00:54:07,386 --> 00:54:10,013
We've got a spot for you
right over here.

787
00:54:15,268 --> 00:54:16,394
(PAGER BEEPING)

788
00:54:18,396 --> 00:54:20,856
Twenty-five years,
huh?

789
00:54:21,816 --> 00:54:23,442
That's quite a
prideful thing.

790
00:54:25,694 --> 00:54:27,154
This we don't need.

791
00:54:30,532 --> 00:54:33,910
You know something?
There's a little too much
bounce on your nose.

792
00:54:33,994 --> 00:54:35,120
We don't want that.

793
00:54:35,161 --> 00:54:38,581
Would you be opposed
to just the slightest
touch of base?

794
00:54:58,808 --> 00:55:01,018
PHOTOGRAPHER: Very nice.
Sit up a bit straighter.

795
00:55:01,060 --> 00:55:04,188
Good. A little bit of a smile.
And excellent.

796
00:55:04,230 --> 00:55:06,023
Keep thinking those
patriotic thoughts.

797
00:55:06,106 --> 00:55:08,275
And that's good.
Little straighter.

798
00:55:08,358 --> 00:55:10,736
Beautiful. Excellent.
You're gonna love that one.

799
00:55:10,819 --> 00:55:11,862
Stop.

800
00:55:14,489 --> 00:55:16,032
Stop.

801
00:55:22,079 --> 00:55:24,206
Mr. Hanssen,
we can get another tie.

802
00:55:25,374 --> 00:55:27,543
I don't like being
scrutinized.

803
00:55:31,630 --> 00:55:33,131
Hey, I found you.

804
00:55:34,090 --> 00:55:35,717
I was on my way
to the range,

805
00:55:35,800 --> 00:55:37,593
so I called
your office.

806
00:55:38,761 --> 00:55:43,808
I thought I might finally
see if you're the dead shot
I've been hearing you are.

807
00:55:44,934 --> 00:55:46,727
Look, maybe
some other time, Rich.

808
00:55:46,810 --> 00:55:49,146
I'm not in the mood
just now.

809
00:55:49,187 --> 00:55:52,232
Me, neither.
Let's take it out
on some targets.

810
00:55:55,068 --> 00:55:56,194
Fine.

811
00:56:00,907 --> 00:56:01,866
<i>(GUN FIRING)</i>

812
00:56:20,841 --> 00:56:22,134
RICH: Shameful.

813
00:56:24,803 --> 00:56:26,096
Double or nothing?

814
00:57:10,762 --> 00:57:11,847
(WHISPERING)
Wrong pocket.

815
00:57:31,740 --> 00:57:32,741
(DOOR BEEPING)
Oh, shit.

816
00:57:55,178 --> 00:57:58,347
Holy Mary, Mother of God,
pray for us sinners now,

817
00:57:58,431 --> 00:58:00,433
and at the hour
of our death. Amen.

818
00:58:04,395 --> 00:58:05,562
(KEYS JINGLING)

819
00:58:06,480 --> 00:58:07,481
Oh.

820
00:58:07,523 --> 00:58:08,649
Sorry.

821
00:58:09,483 --> 00:58:10,567
How'd it go?

822
00:58:11,318 --> 00:58:12,569
It didn't.

823
00:58:14,112 --> 00:58:17,323
I don't know
why they thought
I'd just sit there

824
00:58:17,365 --> 00:58:20,117
while some
faggot photographer
got his jollies.

825
00:58:21,994 --> 00:58:23,162
I've got work to do.

826
00:58:23,412 --> 00:58:24,997
Should I reschedule it?

827
00:58:25,706 --> 00:58:26,749
No. Mmm-mmm.

828
00:58:52,147 --> 00:58:55,483
(ZIPPERS ZIPPING)

829
00:58:55,859 --> 00:58:58,111
(COMPUTER POWERING UP)

830
00:59:11,623 --> 00:59:12,707
Hey.

831
00:59:13,917 --> 00:59:15,502
Have you been
in my briefcase?

832
00:59:15,919 --> 00:59:19,046
No. I just had to move it
so it wouldn't get soaked.

833
00:59:19,088 --> 00:59:20,548
The water was everywhere.

834
00:59:21,674 --> 00:59:23,425
Why? Did I
put it back wrong?

835
00:59:29,723 --> 00:59:30,724
Sir?

836
00:59:32,517 --> 00:59:34,060
All right, let's go.

837
00:59:41,567 --> 00:59:43,486
Would you like to
hear some music, sir?

838
00:59:44,069 --> 00:59:47,072
Yes, I'm in the mood
for some Andrews Sisters.

839
00:59:47,990 --> 00:59:49,449
They got any in here?

840
00:59:50,367 --> 00:59:51,701
Not to my knowledge, sir.

841
00:59:52,244 --> 00:59:53,411
I didn't think so.

842
00:59:56,372 --> 00:59:57,874
That's good.

843
01:00:04,630 --> 01:00:06,673
You've got until 5:00.
AGENT: Yes, sir.

844
01:00:12,429 --> 01:00:13,555
Clear.

845
01:00:24,857 --> 01:00:25,983
Jesus.

846
01:00:26,984 --> 01:00:30,112
This guy could park
at the bottom of the Potomac
and come out firing.

847
01:00:38,578 --> 01:00:40,329
MAN: Yes, sir.
He just arrived.

848
01:00:41,622 --> 01:00:44,667
Oh, I see.
Yes, sir, I understand.

849
01:00:46,919 --> 01:00:48,003
Absolutely.

850
01:00:48,545 --> 01:00:49,671
Yes, sir.

851
01:00:52,674 --> 01:00:54,300
I've got some bad news,
Agent Hanssen.

852
01:00:54,342 --> 01:00:56,219
We're gonna have to
cut this meeting short.

853
01:00:56,427 --> 01:00:57,804
I don't understand.

854
01:00:57,845 --> 01:00:58,888
That was my superior.

855
01:00:58,930 --> 01:01:01,223
He's called me into
an emergency meeting.
I'm sorry.

856
01:01:01,307 --> 01:01:03,684
Does he know that I'm here?
Yes, sir.

857
01:01:04,185 --> 01:01:07,104
Does he know who I am?
I made that clear
to him, sir, yes.

858
01:01:07,187 --> 01:01:09,147
He wants me to reschedule
at your convenience.

859
01:01:09,231 --> 01:01:10,857
No, thanks.
Sir?

860
01:01:12,025 --> 01:01:14,778
This visit
was a courtesy.
Let's go.

861
01:01:14,861 --> 01:01:16,362
Maybe there's somebody else
who can show us around.

862
01:01:16,446 --> 01:01:17,822
Get the car.

863
01:01:38,132 --> 01:01:39,509
Boss, I'm sorry.

864
01:01:39,550 --> 01:01:42,720
I was doing you a favor
bringing you along.
I know I spoke out of turn.

865
01:01:42,762 --> 01:01:46,181
When somebody takes
a shit on you,
you don't reschedule.

866
01:01:46,682 --> 01:01:49,935
He wasn't called in
to any meeting.
It's a power play.

867
01:01:50,727 --> 01:01:52,020
I didn't see it
that way.

868
01:01:52,103 --> 01:01:54,481
Well, that's why
you're still a clerk.

869
01:01:54,564 --> 01:01:55,690
(ANNOYED)
What's he looking for?

870
01:01:55,773 --> 01:01:56,983
(TRUNK DOOR SLAMS)
GUARD: Okay.

871
01:01:57,734 --> 01:01:59,360
(SIGHING)
Just take me back
to the office.

872
01:02:07,075 --> 01:02:08,118
<i>(PHONE RINGING)</i>

873
01:02:08,202 --> 01:02:10,620
<i>Plesac
They're on their way back.</i>

874
01:02:10,704 --> 01:02:11,663
Uh-huh.

875
01:02:11,746 --> 01:02:12,998
The meeting
only took 20 minutes.

876
01:02:13,081 --> 01:02:14,541
They're on Wilson Boulevard,
heading back.

877
01:02:20,838 --> 01:02:21,881
Sew it up.

878
01:02:22,882 --> 01:02:25,134
Sir?
We're aborting. Sew it up.

879
01:02:26,635 --> 01:02:28,804
How about that?
The Parkway's wide open.

880
01:02:28,845 --> 01:02:30,555
I hate the Parkway.
Take E Street.

881
01:02:30,597 --> 01:02:33,475
There's construction
on E Street. I heard that
on the radio this morning.

882
01:02:33,475 --> 01:02:34,851
So take Constitution.

883
01:02:35,393 --> 01:02:38,521
Sir, I'm SSG.
We tail people for a living.

884
01:02:39,147 --> 01:02:40,314
The Parkway's faster.

885
01:02:41,232 --> 01:02:42,983
Is that a fact?

886
01:02:56,329 --> 01:02:58,206
MAN: Let's go, let's go.

887
01:02:58,373 --> 01:03:01,584
I just paged him.
Where are we?
I'm not sure yet.

888
01:03:01,625 --> 01:03:02,877
Maybe screwed.

889
01:03:03,419 --> 01:03:06,588
(HORNS BLARING)

890
01:03:13,303 --> 01:03:14,387
Lmbecile.

891
01:03:14,596 --> 01:03:15,555
I'm sorry.

892
01:03:16,472 --> 01:03:18,558
Idiot.
I'm sorry.

893
01:03:19,433 --> 01:03:21,644
Is this
what they teach you
in ghosting school?

894
01:03:22,520 --> 01:03:25,230
No wonder the Bureau
can never find anyone.

895
01:03:26,106 --> 01:03:27,983
(HONKING)
Hey, just relax.

896
01:03:30,068 --> 01:03:32,320
Don't tell me to relax.

897
01:03:40,203 --> 01:03:41,454
What are you doing?

898
01:03:43,080 --> 01:03:45,124
I can sit here
for an hour.

899
01:03:45,624 --> 01:03:49,461
Or I can walk two blocks,
get on the other side of
this bottleneck by myself,

900
01:03:49,544 --> 01:03:51,963
and take a five-minute
cab ride back to the office.

901
01:03:52,005 --> 01:03:55,341
Now, which do you think
would better serve
the needs of the Bureau?

902
01:03:56,175 --> 01:03:57,844
It's just traffic.

903
01:03:59,345 --> 01:04:00,721
Hello, Hanssen's on foot.

904
01:04:00,846 --> 01:04:01,806
<i>PLESAC: Good God</i>

905
01:04:01,847 --> 01:04:03,891
I put him back at the office
in 10 minutes, best case.

906
01:04:06,810 --> 01:04:08,061
Your boy's killing us.

907
01:04:08,228 --> 01:04:09,604
He'll be fine.

908
01:04:13,441 --> 01:04:16,527
Boss. You gotta get
back in the truck, sir.

909
01:04:16,986 --> 01:04:19,197
Haven't you made
enough mistakes
for one day, Eric?

910
01:04:19,238 --> 01:04:21,282
Now you want to throw in
a traffic violation?

911
01:04:21,324 --> 01:04:23,284
Sir, you have to
get back in the truck.

912
01:04:23,409 --> 01:04:24,827
Well, why should I?

913
01:04:24,868 --> 01:04:27,579
Look, don't kill me, okay?
I did something stupid.

914
01:04:27,663 --> 01:04:29,081
What a shock.

915
01:04:30,165 --> 01:04:31,750
I lied to you, sir.

916
01:04:38,006 --> 01:04:40,967
There isn't any construction
on E Street. I made that up.

917
01:04:41,926 --> 01:04:43,636
What would you
do that for?

918
01:04:44,637 --> 01:04:46,221
Because I need your help.

919
01:04:47,723 --> 01:04:50,559
And I was afraid
to ask if we could
make an extra stop.

920
01:04:52,352 --> 01:04:54,813
I wanted to go back
to the reading room, sir.

921
01:04:54,854 --> 01:04:57,982
The Catholic
Information Center.
I sort of have to.

922
01:04:59,859 --> 01:05:00,985
Why?

923
01:05:06,115 --> 01:05:07,407
It's Juliana.

924
01:05:09,159 --> 01:05:10,911
We've been fighting
all week.

925
01:05:12,120 --> 01:05:13,413
About what?

926
01:05:13,496 --> 01:05:14,622
To be honest, sir,

927
01:05:15,707 --> 01:05:16,666
your church.

928
01:05:18,584 --> 01:05:20,836
She didn't like it, boss.
She didn't get it.

929
01:05:20,920 --> 01:05:23,047
So I wanted to go back
to the reading room.

930
01:05:23,130 --> 01:05:25,090
I thought
there might be some books
I could get for her,

931
01:05:25,174 --> 01:05:26,717
to help her
see things better.

932
01:05:27,217 --> 01:05:30,846
I figured if we were
driving right past,
you might wanna pull in.

933
01:05:31,763 --> 01:05:34,891
It was stupid,
I know.

934
01:05:35,183 --> 01:05:36,434
But there it is.

935
01:05:45,484 --> 01:05:46,985
You swear to God.

936
01:05:47,194 --> 01:05:48,111
Excuse me?

937
01:05:48,195 --> 01:05:49,488
Swear to God

938
01:05:51,198 --> 01:05:53,700
that everything
you just told me is true.

939
01:05:55,660 --> 01:05:56,786
No.

940
01:05:57,453 --> 01:05:58,955
I'm not gonna do that.

941
01:06:00,164 --> 01:06:01,582
I wouldn't lie
about my wife,

942
01:06:02,416 --> 01:06:03,375
or the church.

943
01:06:04,835 --> 01:06:06,295
If you don't know that
by now,

944
01:06:06,378 --> 01:06:10,132
then I sure as hell wouldn't
take the Lord's name in vain
just to prove it to you.

945
01:06:12,467 --> 01:06:16,304
You know something, sir?
You do test people too much.

946
01:06:17,263 --> 01:06:18,306
And I've had it.

947
01:06:20,600 --> 01:06:22,518
I was asking for your help.

948
01:06:23,811 --> 01:06:26,772
Have a nice walk, sir.
I'll see you
back at the office.

949
01:06:34,279 --> 01:06:35,488
(CAR HORN HONKING)

950
01:07:09,519 --> 01:07:10,771
Maybe...

951
01:07:10,854 --> 01:07:11,980
Maybe

952
01:07:12,564 --> 01:07:13,773
I overstepped.

953
01:07:16,150 --> 01:07:17,360
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

954
01:07:18,111 --> 01:07:19,070
Yeah?

955
01:07:19,362 --> 01:07:20,780
O'Neill just
talked him back in.

956
01:07:21,530 --> 01:07:23,908
<i>How'd he manage that?
Hard to say</i>

957
01:07:24,158 --> 01:07:26,285
From here it looks
like he may have
proposed marriage.

958
01:07:29,288 --> 01:07:31,164
He talked him
back in the car.

959
01:07:45,302 --> 01:07:46,553
(SIGHS)

960
01:07:56,980 --> 01:07:58,898
This needs to be mailed.

961
01:08:00,316 --> 01:08:02,151
You're not
coming in, sir?

962
01:08:02,234 --> 01:08:03,986
I don't have to
account to you, do I?

963
01:08:04,278 --> 01:08:05,237
No, sir.

964
01:08:07,531 --> 01:08:08,490
(DOOR SLAMS)

965
01:08:08,657 --> 01:08:10,409
(FOOTSTEPS FADING)

966
01:08:20,167 --> 01:08:23,087
(KETTLE WHISTLING)

967
01:08:37,266 --> 01:08:40,102
<i>(WOMAN MO ANING)</i>

968
01:08:49,403 --> 01:08:51,821
<i>(COUPLE PANTING)</i>

969
01:08:54,783 --> 01:08:55,742
(DOOR OPENS)

970
01:08:56,409 --> 01:08:58,161
Hey.
Hi.

971
01:09:00,329 --> 01:09:01,580
What are you watching?

972
01:09:01,622 --> 01:09:05,084
Nothing.
Just a training tape
on surveillance.

973
01:09:07,169 --> 01:09:09,921
Hanssen wanted me to make sure
the transfer was okay.

974
01:09:11,965 --> 01:09:12,924
Oh.

975
01:09:15,677 --> 01:09:19,097
Would you mind getting
the rest of the groceries
for me, honey?

976
01:09:19,180 --> 01:09:21,015
Just a few more bags
in the car.

977
01:09:23,517 --> 01:09:26,437
How was school?
It was fine. I'm just tired.

978
01:10:00,009 --> 01:10:01,052
Jule.

979
01:10:02,053 --> 01:10:04,096
A training tape
on surveillance?

980
01:10:04,763 --> 01:10:06,515
This is not
what it looks like.

981
01:10:06,557 --> 01:10:08,892
What it looks like
is he's making
pornos of Bonnie,

982
01:10:08,934 --> 01:10:10,852
except she doesn't
know about it.

983
01:10:12,062 --> 01:10:15,482
Everybody told me,
when you marry the Bureau,
things get weird. The cases.

984
01:10:15,523 --> 01:10:17,692
But they never told me
about this.

985
01:10:18,317 --> 01:10:20,319
This has nothing
to do with a case.

986
01:10:21,237 --> 01:10:22,196
Oh.

987
01:10:22,279 --> 01:10:26,158
So you weren't just
steaming open his mail?
He gave it to you?

988
01:10:29,077 --> 01:10:30,120
I gotta go.

989
01:10:31,746 --> 01:10:32,747
Do you trust me?

990
01:10:32,789 --> 01:10:33,748
(SIGHS)

991
01:10:34,290 --> 01:10:35,416
Yes.

992
01:10:35,500 --> 01:10:37,335
'Cause I think you've got
this idea somehow

993
01:10:37,418 --> 01:10:38,753
that telling me
the truth about him

994
01:10:38,836 --> 01:10:42,173
would mean
you were betraying
your country or something.

995
01:10:42,256 --> 01:10:43,340
It wouldn't.

996
01:10:47,010 --> 01:10:48,387
It's okay.

997
01:10:49,096 --> 01:10:51,389
He's a creep.
I knew that already.

998
01:10:52,307 --> 01:10:53,558
It's just...

999
01:10:54,642 --> 01:10:57,520
He's been in our home.
We keep fighting about him.

1000
01:10:58,980 --> 01:11:01,065
I'd just like to know
what this is.

1001
01:11:03,109 --> 01:11:04,735
Can't you tell me?

1002
01:11:07,321 --> 01:11:08,447
Please?

1003
01:11:20,041 --> 01:11:21,876
I don't know
when I'll be back.

1004
01:11:25,462 --> 01:11:26,380
(DOOR CLOSING)

1005
01:11:26,880 --> 01:11:30,175
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

1006
01:11:31,885 --> 01:11:34,387
I think my wife
just read herself
into the case.

1007
01:11:40,935 --> 01:11:43,646
That was a colossally
stupid thing to do!

1008
01:11:43,979 --> 01:11:46,065
You could jeopardize
this entire investigation!

1009
01:11:46,148 --> 01:11:47,191
Are you an idiot?

1010
01:11:47,274 --> 01:11:49,109
You know,
you're as much to blame
for this as anybody.

1011
01:11:49,192 --> 01:11:50,402
I'm telling
so many lies now,

1012
01:11:50,485 --> 01:11:51,778
I can't keep 'em
straight anymore.

1013
01:11:51,862 --> 01:11:53,279
You want to make
things easier?

1014
01:11:53,363 --> 01:11:55,281
The next time Hanssen
gives you a package,

1015
01:11:55,365 --> 01:11:56,783
and he tells you
to mail it,

1016
01:11:56,908 --> 01:11:57,867
you mail it.

1017
01:12:04,456 --> 01:12:06,375
That package was re-sealed
as you found it, right?

1018
01:12:06,458 --> 01:12:07,459
Yes.

1019
01:12:07,543 --> 01:12:09,002
There's no trace that
it had ever been opened?

1020
01:12:09,086 --> 01:12:11,213
Nothing that would
ever arouse suspicion
on the other end?

1021
01:12:11,296 --> 01:12:12,881
No, I posted it
from the Bureau
five minutes ago.

1022
01:12:12,964 --> 01:12:14,215
It was pristine.

1023
01:12:14,340 --> 01:12:15,467
We'll see.

1024
01:12:21,222 --> 01:12:22,515
Look,

1025
01:12:23,891 --> 01:12:26,852
I'm sorry you're having
problems at home.

1026
01:12:26,935 --> 01:12:29,104
I'd offer you some advice,
but it wouldn't be worth much.

1027
01:12:29,146 --> 01:12:31,064
I don't even have a cat.

1028
01:12:31,898 --> 01:12:33,066
All I can tell you

1029
01:12:33,400 --> 01:12:35,777
is you keep
your head on straight
and you do your job.

1030
01:12:35,818 --> 01:12:39,280
It's your best shot
at getting this over with.
Understand?

1031
01:12:40,198 --> 01:12:42,241
We pulled 300 pages
of classified material

1032
01:12:42,324 --> 01:12:45,286
out of a Lawn and Leaf bag
from his trunk today.

1033
01:12:46,203 --> 01:12:48,872
And quite a bit
of correspondence
from the Palm Pilot.

1034
01:12:49,414 --> 01:12:50,957
His next drop appears
to be imminent.

1035
01:12:50,999 --> 01:12:53,668
Unless, of course,
somebody does something
to make him suspicious.

1036
01:12:54,044 --> 01:12:55,003
Right.

1037
01:12:55,128 --> 01:12:56,087
Right.

1038
01:13:01,717 --> 01:13:03,093
I really should be
getting back to this.

1039
01:13:03,469 --> 01:13:04,595
Yeah, okay.

1040
01:13:08,640 --> 01:13:09,766
Can I ask you
something?

1041
01:13:10,642 --> 01:13:11,601
Sure.

1042
01:13:12,435 --> 01:13:13,853
Is it worth it?

1043
01:13:16,439 --> 01:13:17,857
Being an agent.

1044
01:13:18,608 --> 01:13:20,067
What it costs.

1045
01:13:20,610 --> 01:13:22,361
Do you think
it's worth it?

1046
01:13:24,780 --> 01:13:26,657
Ask me
when we've caught him.

1047
01:13:41,253 --> 01:13:43,797
Eric.
Yes, boss?

1048
01:13:45,257 --> 01:13:47,968
Come in here.
I want to show you
something.

1049
01:13:56,226 --> 01:13:58,978
This is the address of
my mechanic in Manassas.

1050
01:13:59,020 --> 01:14:01,522
I'm dropping my car off
on Monday.

1051
01:14:01,856 --> 01:14:04,608
I need you to pick me up
and bring me in to work.

1052
01:14:04,692 --> 01:14:07,569
No later than 8:15.

1053
01:14:09,071 --> 01:14:10,781
Is something wrong
with your car, sir?

1054
01:14:10,864 --> 01:14:14,034
Yeah. I'm having it swept
for electronic devices.

1055
01:14:14,534 --> 01:14:15,743
Oh, yeah?

1056
01:14:15,827 --> 01:14:19,455
Been sensing signal bursts
coming through
my radio lately,

1057
01:14:19,747 --> 01:14:22,708
and car alarms go off
when I drive past.

1058
01:14:23,876 --> 01:14:27,462
It's not beneath
the Russians to track me.

1059
01:14:27,921 --> 01:14:29,798
I'm tailed all the time.

1060
01:14:32,592 --> 01:14:34,135
They know how much I know.

1061
01:14:34,552 --> 01:14:35,762
Yes, sir.

1062
01:14:37,096 --> 01:14:38,556
You know this movie?

1063
01:14:49,191 --> 01:14:51,318
(INAUDIBLE)

1064
01:14:54,446 --> 01:14:56,656
She's very appealing.

1065
01:14:57,407 --> 01:14:59,200
Yes, sir.
I've always thought so.

1066
01:15:07,916 --> 01:15:09,584
Close the door
on your way out.

1067
01:15:20,595 --> 01:15:22,179
(SIGHS SOFTLY)

1068
01:15:23,681 --> 01:15:24,848
(PAGER BEEPS)

1069
01:15:46,118 --> 01:15:47,411
What happened?

1070
01:15:48,453 --> 01:15:51,331
We just got
the encryption
off this one.

1071
01:15:51,414 --> 01:15:54,167
His last letter
to his handlers in
the SVR two days ago.

1072
01:15:54,709 --> 01:15:56,294
He's going to ground,
isn't he?

1073
01:15:56,586 --> 01:15:57,503
Yes.

1074
01:15:58,337 --> 01:15:59,755
<i>ERIC: Then we're dead</i>

1075
01:16:01,215 --> 01:16:05,761
"Dear friends, I thank you
for your assistance
these many years.

1076
01:16:05,844 --> 01:16:09,181
"It seems, however,
that my greatest utility
to you has come to an end,

1077
01:16:09,264 --> 01:16:12,350
"and it is time to seclude
myself from active service.

1078
01:16:12,767 --> 01:16:16,688
"Since communicating last,
and one wonders
if because of it,

1079
01:16:16,771 --> 01:16:20,566
"I have been promoted
to a higher do-nothing
senior executive job,

1080
01:16:20,691 --> 01:16:24,528
"outside of regular access
to information within the
counterintelligence program.

1081
01:16:25,654 --> 01:16:27,739
"It is as if
I am being isolated.

1082
01:16:30,200 --> 01:16:32,244
"Furthermore,
I believe I have detected

1083
01:16:32,285 --> 01:16:35,705
"repeated bursting
radio signal emanations
from my vehicle.

1084
01:16:35,788 --> 01:16:37,582
"I have not found
their source,

1085
01:16:37,582 --> 01:16:40,126
"but as you wisely do,
I will leave this alone.

1086
01:16:40,334 --> 01:16:43,045
"For knowledge of their
existence is sufficient.

1087
01:16:43,754 --> 01:16:46,465
"Amusing,
the games children play.

1088
01:16:49,176 --> 01:16:53,054
"In this, however,
I strongly suspect that
you should have concerns

1089
01:16:53,263 --> 01:16:55,223
"for the integrity
of your compartment

1090
01:16:55,306 --> 01:16:58,226
"concerning knowledge
of my efforts on your behalf.

1091
01:16:58,309 --> 01:17:00,811
"Something has aroused
the sleeping tiger.

1092
01:17:00,895 --> 01:17:02,813
"Perhaps you know
better than I.

1093
01:17:04,064 --> 01:17:06,775
<i>"Life is full
of its ups and downs</i>

1094
01:17:08,443 --> 01:17:10,153
"Yours truly, Ramon."

1095
01:17:18,619 --> 01:17:22,998
(SOBBING QUIETLY)

1096
01:17:26,960 --> 01:17:29,463
<i>BURROUGHS: Okay, if he
doesn't make another drop,
what do we have?</i>

1097
01:17:29,546 --> 01:17:31,047
We've got
the Palm Pilot.

1098
01:17:32,132 --> 01:17:34,509
It still gives us
conspiracy to
commit espionage.

1099
01:17:34,509 --> 01:17:36,427
Until he walks
into a court
with a lawyer

1100
01:17:36,469 --> 01:17:38,554
who says everything
on the Palm Pilot
was just notes

1101
01:17:38,638 --> 01:17:41,182
for a spy novel
he was planning to write.

1102
01:17:41,932 --> 01:17:43,601
What about the evidence
in his trunk?

1103
01:17:43,684 --> 01:17:45,394
Unauthorized possession
of classified material.

1104
01:17:45,477 --> 01:17:46,603
That's five years.

1105
01:17:47,479 --> 01:17:48,897
Hardly enough
to make him talk.

1106
01:17:48,939 --> 01:17:50,357
Maybe we just
keep promoting him.

1107
01:17:50,399 --> 01:17:52,067
Might be the only way
to keep him from retiring.

1108
01:17:52,150 --> 01:17:53,193
Shit.

1109
01:17:53,276 --> 01:17:54,736
He's outside
your apartment.

1110
01:17:55,153 --> 01:17:57,572
What?
He's parked outside
your apartment.

1111
01:17:57,613 --> 01:17:58,656
Just pulled up.

1112
01:17:59,031 --> 01:18:02,076
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1113
01:18:02,159 --> 01:18:03,077
(BEEPS)

1114
01:18:03,827 --> 01:18:04,912
It's him.

1115
01:18:07,873 --> 01:18:09,166
How drunk did he sound?

1116
01:18:09,249 --> 01:18:10,792
He wasn't slurring
or anything.

1117
01:18:10,834 --> 01:18:13,211
Maybe a little
surlier than usual,
but that's about it.

1118
01:18:14,379 --> 01:18:15,630
The guy's melting down.

1119
01:18:15,672 --> 01:18:16,839
That would bother me
a lot less

1120
01:18:16,923 --> 01:18:18,674
if he didn't have
a dozen guns
in his trunk.

1121
01:18:20,468 --> 01:18:22,595
Drop me off here, okay?
It's right around the corner.

1122
01:18:22,678 --> 01:18:23,721
I know where it is.

1123
01:18:38,443 --> 01:18:39,485
(TAPPING ON GLASS)

1124
01:18:41,445 --> 01:18:43,155
We got a team
on his tail, right?

1125
01:18:43,197 --> 01:18:44,156
Uh-huh.

1126
01:18:44,907 --> 01:18:46,366
Can we pull 'em back?

1127
01:18:47,117 --> 01:18:48,994
Why would I want
to do that?

1128
01:18:49,369 --> 01:18:50,704
I think I can still
work him.

1129
01:18:51,079 --> 01:18:52,539
I think I can get him
to make that drop.

1130
01:18:52,622 --> 01:18:55,083
Do you need me to read
that letter again, Eric?
There is no drop.

1131
01:18:55,166 --> 01:18:56,167
He's going to ground.

1132
01:18:56,251 --> 01:18:58,336
No, he's dying to make it.
We just have to
make him feel safe.

1133
01:18:58,419 --> 01:19:00,421
What if he's made you?
What if he has?

1134
01:19:00,504 --> 01:19:03,090
Bumper-locking him's
not gonna make me any safer.

1135
01:19:03,757 --> 01:19:04,842
Please.

1136
01:19:05,551 --> 01:19:06,969
I can handle him.

1137
01:19:08,428 --> 01:19:09,554
Okay.

1138
01:19:11,348 --> 01:19:12,682
I'll call Dean.

1139
01:19:37,205 --> 01:19:38,790
Ten minutes,
as promised.

1140
01:19:39,665 --> 01:19:41,459
Caught me coming
right out of the Metro.

1141
01:19:41,542 --> 01:19:43,085
Why didn't you drive?

1142
01:19:43,294 --> 01:19:44,587
Juliana needed the car.

1143
01:19:45,587 --> 01:19:46,839
I felt like walking,
anyway.

1144
01:19:48,048 --> 01:19:50,175
Why? Something
on your mind?

1145
01:19:50,842 --> 01:19:52,219
Not especially.

1146
01:19:55,889 --> 01:19:59,058
Now, get in.
I want some company.
Sure.

1147
01:20:05,397 --> 01:20:08,233
You been drinking, sir?
Can I trust you?

1148
01:20:11,236 --> 01:20:12,487
Of course.

1149
01:20:14,656 --> 01:20:16,199
Don't you know that?

1150
01:20:20,119 --> 01:20:22,455
I don't know
what I know anymore.

1151
01:20:29,461 --> 01:20:31,254
<i>(NEAR YOU PLAYING ON STEREO)</i>

1152
01:20:47,686 --> 01:20:48,645
(EXHALES)

1153
01:20:52,649 --> 01:20:54,984
Is this the music
of your childhood
or something?

1154
01:20:58,362 --> 01:21:01,574
That's the music of
my father's childhood.

1155
01:21:13,877 --> 01:21:15,378
What's in Rock Creek?

1156
01:21:18,673 --> 01:21:20,591
I like the park
at night.

1157
01:21:49,868 --> 01:21:50,952
(TURNS OFF STEREO)

1158
01:21:51,620 --> 01:21:55,415
I have to be sure
that I can trust you.

1159
01:21:57,834 --> 01:22:00,211
Why don't we go
back to the office?
You can polygraph me.

1160
01:22:00,378 --> 01:22:01,420
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

1161
01:22:04,381 --> 01:22:06,091
You heard
of Aldrich Ames?

1162
01:22:07,301 --> 01:22:08,302
Of course.

1163
01:22:08,552 --> 01:22:11,221
Worst spy
in U.S. History.

1164
01:22:11,513 --> 01:22:17,185
(PUNCTUATING) Sold
$2.5 million worth of
information to the Soviets,

1165
01:22:18,311 --> 01:22:21,814
and passed every polygraph
the Agency gave him.

1166
01:22:26,819 --> 01:22:29,071
But he never would have
gotten past me.

1167
01:22:32,073 --> 01:22:33,950
I can read anyone.

1168
01:22:34,409 --> 01:22:36,869
(PAGER BEEPING)

1169
01:22:36,953 --> 01:22:39,580
I'm getting really
tired of that pager.

1170
01:22:43,250 --> 01:22:44,543
What are we doing?

1171
01:22:44,585 --> 01:22:47,045
I told you,
the FBI's a gun culture.

1172
01:22:49,506 --> 01:22:52,217
You can't advance there
unless you can shoot.

1173
01:23:16,489 --> 01:23:17,615
Boss?

1174
01:23:39,635 --> 01:23:41,846
They test you
at 25 yards,

1175
01:23:42,430 --> 01:23:43,556
15 yards,

1176
01:23:44,306 --> 01:23:45,683
7 yards and 5 yards.

1177
01:23:45,766 --> 01:23:46,725
(GUN FIRES)

1178
01:23:47,226 --> 01:23:49,478
What are you doing?
You want to be an agent
or don't you?

1179
01:23:50,604 --> 01:23:54,816
Prone. Left hand,
right hand. Five yards
with gun in holster.

1180
01:23:54,858 --> 01:23:57,110
You get 3 seconds
to fire 5 shots.

1181
01:23:57,902 --> 01:24:00,529
What are you doing?
Who was calling you
in the car?

1182
01:24:00,571 --> 01:24:01,572
What?

1183
01:24:01,655 --> 01:24:03,657
I need to know
if I can trust you.

1184
01:24:04,241 --> 01:24:05,492
Put the gun down, Boss.

1185
01:24:05,576 --> 01:24:07,703
Who was calling?
Put the fucking gun down!

1186
01:24:07,786 --> 01:24:10,122
I need to know
if I can trust you.

1187
01:24:14,959 --> 01:24:15,919
(GUN CLICKS)

1188
01:24:20,006 --> 01:24:21,590
Can I trust you?

1189
01:24:21,966 --> 01:24:22,883
Jesus!

1190
01:24:23,926 --> 01:24:26,303
God's sakes,
what is wrong with you?

1191
01:24:28,430 --> 01:24:29,765
Look around you,
boss.

1192
01:24:30,724 --> 01:24:32,017
It's just us out here.

1193
01:24:32,851 --> 01:24:35,562
Nobody's tailing you,
there isn't any GPS
on your car,

1194
01:24:35,645 --> 01:24:38,064
and I'm not a foreign agent
trying to work you.

1195
01:24:40,399 --> 01:24:41,817
You don't matter
that much.

1196
01:24:45,070 --> 01:24:48,532
The page was from Juliana,
obviously. My wife.

1197
01:24:49,950 --> 01:24:52,327
She's trying to reach me
because I told her
I'd be home by now,

1198
01:24:52,369 --> 01:24:53,703
and because we're
in another fight,

1199
01:24:53,828 --> 01:24:55,538
caused by you,
as usual.

1200
01:24:57,373 --> 01:25:00,209
Thanks for dropping by
unannounced and lecturing her
about Opus Dei.

1201
01:25:00,251 --> 01:25:01,502
That was real helpful.

1202
01:25:01,836 --> 01:25:04,129
Oh, and thanks for staring
at her in church
like she was from Mars.

1203
01:25:04,213 --> 01:25:05,964
That also worked out great.

1204
01:25:07,090 --> 01:25:08,383
Let me guess.

1205
01:25:08,925 --> 01:25:10,552
You were testing her, too.

1206
01:25:13,930 --> 01:25:17,100
You know,
she asked me this morning
why you're like this.

1207
01:25:17,266 --> 01:25:19,519
Why you grind
everybody so hard.

1208
01:25:20,144 --> 01:25:22,313
I had all these
answers ready.

1209
01:25:22,354 --> 01:25:23,856
"He's misunderstood.

1210
01:25:23,898 --> 01:25:26,191
"He's trying to fix the Bureau
and no one will listen.

1211
01:25:26,275 --> 01:25:28,527
"He was born
in the wrong century.
His father was a jerk."

1212
01:25:28,527 --> 01:25:29,820
I got a whole list.

1213
01:25:30,320 --> 01:25:31,780
But you know
something, sir?

1214
01:25:33,031 --> 01:25:34,365
At the end of the day,

1215
01:25:35,074 --> 01:25:36,242
it's all crap.

1216
01:25:37,243 --> 01:25:39,162
You are who you are.

1217
01:25:40,788 --> 01:25:42,665
The why doesn't mean
a thing, does it?

1218
01:25:44,333 --> 01:25:45,793
(SNAPPING)
Does it?

1219
01:25:58,513 --> 01:25:59,555
I

1220
01:25:59,931 --> 01:26:00,890
matter

1221
01:26:01,390 --> 01:26:02,349
plenty.

1222
01:26:39,258 --> 01:26:40,218
(PHONE RINGS)

1223
01:26:40,301 --> 01:26:41,302
Yes, Eric?

1224
01:26:41,385 --> 01:26:43,304
Put the tail back on him.
He'll make the drop.

1225
01:26:43,387 --> 01:26:44,805
Tomorrow. Maybe even tonight.

1226
01:26:45,055 --> 01:26:46,265
You're not burned?

1227
01:26:48,016 --> 01:26:49,267
No, I'm not burned.

1228
01:26:49,351 --> 01:26:50,685
<i>Okay We're on it</i>

1229
01:27:06,533 --> 01:27:08,869
(PRINTER WHINING)

1230
01:30:16,374 --> 01:30:17,834
(DOG HOWLING)

1231
01:30:51,281 --> 01:30:52,449
(RADIO CRACKLING)

1232
01:30:53,825 --> 01:30:56,744
(GUNS BEING LOADED)

1233
01:31:25,062 --> 01:31:26,563
FBI!
FBI! Don't move!

1234
01:31:26,647 --> 01:31:28,023
Don't move! Don't move!

1235
01:31:28,106 --> 01:31:29,983
Guns won't be necessary.

1236
01:31:30,942 --> 01:31:32,110
Guns won't be necessary.

1237
01:31:32,193 --> 01:31:34,028
You have anything
in your pockets
I should know about?

1238
01:31:34,112 --> 01:31:35,613
No.

1239
01:31:36,447 --> 01:31:37,990
Do you have
a weapon on you?
No.

1240
01:31:40,618 --> 01:31:42,495
So, this is
how it goes.

1241
01:32:06,683 --> 01:32:08,852
Maybe now
you'll listen.

1242
01:32:09,353 --> 01:32:11,563
It's a sad day
for all of us, Bob.

1243
01:32:42,591 --> 01:32:43,676
Hi.

1244
01:32:44,385 --> 01:32:45,344
Hi.

1245
01:32:58,272 --> 01:32:59,398
Is everything okay?

1246
01:33:00,024 --> 01:33:01,108
Yeah.

1247
01:33:11,493 --> 01:33:13,078
Everything's fine.

1248
01:33:19,500 --> 01:33:20,626
I'm sorry.

1249
01:33:31,219 --> 01:33:33,263
PLESAC: Can I give you
some advice, Bob?

1250
01:33:38,101 --> 01:33:39,810
I've been in
on a few of these now.

1251
01:33:40,770 --> 01:33:41,729
Nicholson.

1252
01:33:41,979 --> 01:33:42,897
Aldrich Ames.

1253
01:33:44,356 --> 01:33:46,275
It goes a lot easier
if you cooperate.

1254
01:33:46,859 --> 01:33:47,818
On you.

1255
01:33:48,443 --> 01:33:49,528
On your family.

1256
01:33:49,611 --> 01:33:53,114
(CHUCKLES) You really
ought to do an overhaul
on your GPS units, Dean.

1257
01:33:53,698 --> 01:33:56,659
They throw off
a signal burst
through the radio.

1258
01:33:57,118 --> 01:33:58,661
I heard it coming
through mine for weeks.

1259
01:33:58,744 --> 01:34:01,288
Even if all you give them
is why you did it,

1260
01:34:01,831 --> 01:34:03,374
it buys you some goodwill.

1261
01:34:04,583 --> 01:34:06,418
Well, that's what
Ames did at first.

1262
01:34:07,252 --> 01:34:08,337
Just gave up
the why.

1263
01:34:08,378 --> 01:34:10,505
That mustn't have
taken long.

1264
01:34:13,216 --> 01:34:15,593
All Ames cared about
was the money.

1265
01:34:16,552 --> 01:34:18,721
Why else would he
have done it?

1266
01:34:19,263 --> 01:34:21,515
It's not so hard
to guess, is it?

1267
01:34:22,308 --> 01:34:24,310
Considering the human ego.

1268
01:34:28,313 --> 01:34:32,484
Can you imagine,
sitting in a room with a
bunch of your colleagues,

1269
01:34:33,651 --> 01:34:37,071
everybody trying to guess
the identity of a mole

1270
01:34:37,322 --> 01:34:40,283
and all the while,
it's you they're after,

1271
01:34:41,117 --> 01:34:43,202
you they're looking for?

1272
01:34:45,037 --> 01:34:46,121
That must be

1273
01:34:46,747 --> 01:34:48,665
very satisfying,
wouldn't you think?

1274
01:34:51,001 --> 01:34:54,087
Or maybe
he considered himself
a patriot.

1275
01:34:55,129 --> 01:34:57,256
Maybe he saw it
as his duty

1276
01:34:57,340 --> 01:34:59,800
to show us how lax
our security was.

1277
01:34:59,842 --> 01:35:01,927
We can't rule that out
as a possibility.

1278
01:35:02,178 --> 01:35:03,137
Or maybe he...

1279
01:35:10,560 --> 01:35:14,397
Oh, what good does
speculating do? He spied.

1280
01:35:17,442 --> 01:35:18,568
The why

1281
01:35:19,527 --> 01:35:21,112
doesn't mean a thing.

1282
01:35:22,113 --> 01:35:23,405
Does it?

1283
01:35:24,490 --> 01:35:26,283
No, I guess
it doesn't.

1284
01:35:46,677 --> 01:35:47,761
(DOOR BEEPING)

1285
01:36:06,820 --> 01:36:08,447
Two guys on a boat.

1286
01:36:08,572 --> 01:36:09,531
(CHUCKLES)

1287
01:36:15,078 --> 01:36:16,454
You see the Director's
press conference?

1288
01:36:16,829 --> 01:36:17,789
Yeah.

1289
01:36:19,207 --> 01:36:20,625
Funny about those things.

1290
01:36:21,500 --> 01:36:24,545
He thanked the CIA, and
the U.S. Attorney's office,

1291
01:36:25,421 --> 01:36:27,422
and the Council for
Intelligence Policy,

1292
01:36:27,506 --> 01:36:30,801
but he couldn't thank the guy
we put behind that desk.

1293
01:36:31,426 --> 01:36:33,261
I didn't expect him to.

1294
01:36:35,930 --> 01:36:37,390
I'm headed over
to the field office.

1295
01:36:37,473 --> 01:36:40,434
We still have
two Russian IO's
unaccounted for.

1296
01:36:40,685 --> 01:36:43,062
That mean you won't be
headed over there with me?

1297
01:36:44,188 --> 01:36:45,939
I thought I'd
go home instead.

1298
01:36:48,150 --> 01:36:51,027
You're going to make
agent, Eric. It's set now.

1299
01:36:51,278 --> 01:36:52,612
Isn't that
what you wanted?

1300
01:36:52,988 --> 01:36:53,905
It was.

1301
01:36:54,614 --> 01:36:58,659
Until you came over
to my apartment and saw
the TV dinners and no cat?

1302
01:36:58,910 --> 01:36:59,911
No.

1303
01:37:00,036 --> 01:37:02,246
Most of our agents
are married, you know.

1304
01:37:02,746 --> 01:37:04,790
All their spouses get used
to the life eventually.

1305
01:37:04,832 --> 01:37:06,375
So will Juliana.

1306
01:37:09,002 --> 01:37:10,545
I don't think
I want her to.

1307
01:37:14,257 --> 01:37:15,216
Oh.

1308
01:37:17,635 --> 01:37:19,178
That's different.

1309
01:37:21,055 --> 01:37:22,098
Yeah.

1310
01:37:22,973 --> 01:37:25,059
You do know
what you did here, right?

1311
01:37:26,935 --> 01:37:29,855
That was the worst spy
in American history
you brought down.

1312
01:37:31,439 --> 01:37:33,650
Now you're just
gonna walk away?

1313
01:37:33,900 --> 01:37:36,069
Can you think
of a better time
to walk away?

1314
01:37:36,152 --> 01:37:37,403
Nope.

1315
01:37:40,323 --> 01:37:41,449
So...

1316
01:37:52,500 --> 01:37:54,419
You think it'd be
okay if I...

1317
01:37:55,378 --> 01:37:57,171
Oh, I'd say
you earned it.

1318
01:37:57,422 --> 01:37:58,548
(PEN CLICKING)

1319
01:38:04,219 --> 01:38:05,721
Good luck, Eric.

1320
01:38:06,555 --> 01:38:07,764
You, too.

1321
01:38:09,182 --> 01:38:10,183
(DOOR BEEPS)

1322
01:38:12,143 --> 01:38:13,103
(DOOR CLOSES)

1323
01:38:21,694 --> 01:38:22,903
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

1324
01:38:37,750 --> 01:38:39,085
Pray for me.

1325
01:38:43,214 --> 01:38:44,381
I will.

